Description: Prompt the user on whether they want to do this program. “Yes”
entry means they want to continue. Any other response indicates they will stop the program.
This response is the loop control variable. If the user answers “Yes “then go into the while loop.
Once in the while loop. You are to prompt the user for their last name and two exam scores.
Compute the average exam score. Display last name and average. After the loop, display a count
of the number of students who entered data.
Finally, the last statements within the while loop will ask the user if they want to do this loop
again.
"""

#Prompt user to start program 
print("Would you like to start this program? (Yes or No): ")
program_start = input()

student_count = 0 

while program_start == "Yes":
    print("Enter Last Name: ")
    last_name = input()
    print("Enter Exam 1 Score: ")
    exam__1_score = input()
    print("Enter Exam 2 Score: ")
    exam_2_score = input()
        
    exam_average = (int(exam__1_score) + int(exam_2_score)) / 2 
        
    print("Last Name: ", last_name)
    print("Avg Exam Score: ", exam_average)
    
    student_count += 1 
        
    print("Do you wish to do this program again?")
    program_start = input()
    
print("Number of students: ", student_count)
    
    
    
 
